```sql
create table users (
  id bigint PRIMARY KEY GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY,
  email text unique
);

create table profiles (
  id bigint PRIMARY KEY GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY,
  name text,
  photo text,
  users_id bigint references users
);
```

> An identity column, however, does not guarantee uniqueness. (A sequence normally returns unique values, but a sequence could be reset, or values could be inserted manually into the identity column, as discussed above.) Uniqueness would need to be enforced using a PRIMARY KEY or UNIQUE constraint. https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/ddl-identity-columns.html

